  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who has shown remorse by partially repaying the embezzled $25,000. While crimes of financial breach of trust warrant significant deterrence, the outburst from the gallery calling for a 10-year sentence is disregarded as an external pressure, and per judicial discretion, a sentence of 6 months served in a correctional facility is sufficient to address the severity of the theft while allowing for rehabilitation given the clean prior record.",
  "verdict": 6
}
